---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../../components/ui/TableOfContents';
import MethodologyCard from '../../components/ui/MethodologyCard.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "datePublished": "2026-07-13",
  "dateModified": "2026-07-13",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much power does a PC draw at idle?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A modern gaming PC typically draws between 45W and 80W at idle. This power draw is composed of CPU standby C-states, GPU idle clocks, motherboard chipset activity, and RGB cooling configurations."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<Layout
  title="PC Idle Power Consumption: Optimization & C-States — PSUCheck"
  description="Learn what causes idle power draw in gaming PCs. Discover how BIOS configurations, Windows power schemes, and C-states optimize desktop idle efficiency."
  schema={faqSchema}
>
  <article class="guide-article">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="guide-header">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <a href="/methodology" class="badge badge-safe" style="text-decoration:none;">✓ Sizing Methodology Verified</a>
          <span>Updated: July 13, 2026</span>
          <span style="margin: 0 0.5rem; opacity: 0.5;">•</span>
          <span>1 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1>PC Idle Power: Causes &amp; Optimizations</h1>
        <p class="guide-lead">
          Computers spend most of their lives idling. This guide explores the causes of
          idle power consumption and how to configure your system for maximum savings.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="guide-layout">
        <main class="guide-content" id="main-content">
          <h2>Components of Idle Power</h2>
          <p>
            Even when you are just viewing your desktop, components are active:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>CPU Package:</strong> Modern CPUs drop core states (C-states) down, drawing 10W-25W.</li>
            <li><strong>GPU Idle State:</strong> The graphics card clocks down memory and core speeds, drawing 10W-20W (unless running multiple high-refresh monitors).</li>
            <li><strong>Motherboard & Chipset:</strong> VRM overheads, SATA lines, USB hubs, and chipsets draw 15W-25W.</li>
            <li><strong>Fans & RGB:</strong> A single 120mm fan draws ~2W; complex RGB cooling hubs can draw 10W-15W.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>The Impact of High-Refresh Monitors</h2>
          <p>
            Connecting multiple monitors or running a single panel at 240Hz+ often prevents the GPU from entering
            its lowest power state, causing the card to draw up to 40W permanently at idle.
          </p>

          <h2>BIOS & OS Optimizations</h2>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Enable Global C-States:</strong> Ensure AMD Cool'n'Quiet or Intel SpeedShift is set to 'Enabled' in the BIOS.</li>
            <li><strong>PCI Express ASPM:</strong> Enable Active State Power Management in BIOS to let PCIe lanes sleep when idle.</li>
            <li><strong>Windows Balanced Profile:</strong> Avoid using 'High Performance' power profiles, which force the CPU cores to stay locked at max boost frequencies.</li>
          </ol>

          <div style="margin-top:3rem;">
            <a href="/psu-calculator" class="btn btn-primary">Check system idle profiles</a>
          </div>
        </main>

        <aside class="guide-sidebar">
          <TableOfContents client:load />
          <MethodologyCard />
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Calculators</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/psu-calculator">⚡ PSU Calculator</a></li>
              <li><a href="/pc-builder">🖥️ PC Build Cost Calculator</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Other Guides</h3>
            <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.875rem;">
              <li><a href="/guides/psu-efficiency-guide">80+ Efficiency Guide</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/aio-cooler-power-draw">AIO Cooler Power</a></li>
              <li><a href="/guides/psu-sizing-guide">PSU Sizing Guide</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
.guide-article { padding: 4rem 0; }
.guide-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
.guide-meta { display:flex; gap: 1rem; align-items:center; font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--text-tertiary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.guide-lead { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 65ch; line-height: 1.65; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
.guide-layout { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3rem; }
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .guide-layout { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 8fr) minmax(0, 4fr); }
}
.guide-content h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content p, .guide-content li { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
.guide-content ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
.guide-sidebar { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap: 1.5rem; }
.guide-sidebar .card { padding: 1.25rem; }
</style>
